      "id": "1.",
      "text": "A bar of soap is better than a bottle of shower gel."
    },
    {
      "id": "1.1.",
      "text": "Shower gel is more hygienic, especially for a shared shower"
    },
    {
      "id": "1.1.1.",
      "text": "After one person used a bar of soap there might be hair sticking to it."
    },
    {
      "id": "1.2.",
      "text": "Shower gels generate a lot more plastic packaging which isn\u2019t always responsibly recycled"
    },
    {
      "id": "1.3.",
      "text": "Shower gel has a lot more bulk and water weight so is inefficient to transport/distribute"
    },
    {
      "id": "1.4.",
      "text": "It is difficult to wash your hair with a bar of soap."
    },
    {
      "id": "1.4.1.",
      "text": "Short hair can be just as easily be washed with a soap by just rubbing it over your hair."
    },
    {
      "id": "1.5.",
      "text": "Soap stings your eyes"
    },
    {
      "id": "1.5.1.",
      "text": "A lot of soap does not sting in the eyes."
    },
    {
      "id": "1.5.2.",
      "text": "Shower gel can sting in your eyes too."
    },
    {
      "id": "1.6.",
      "text": "Soap is old-fashioned"
    },
    {
      "id": "1.7.",
      "text": "Soap is more convenient in use (no bottle to unscrew/open"
    },
    {
      "id": "1.8.",
      "text": "A bar of soap lasts longer."
    },
    {
      "id": "1.9.",
      "text": "A bar of soap uses less packaging than shower gel"
    },
    {
      "id": "1.9.1.",
      "text": "Given the immense damage plastic does to the environment, this is a vital factor to consider."
    },
    {
      "id": "1.10.",
      "text": "Soap is cheaper than shower gel"
    },
    {
      "id": "1.11.",
      "text": "It is easier to drop soap in the shower."
    }
